{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845418278,"sessionID":"ses_2875df83bffermztmCZK44qX8H","part":{"id":"prt_d78a22753001KIychA8C0OpmUI","messageID":"msg_d78a218df001EWymHChnVMiMZX","sessionID":"ses_2875df83bffermztmCZK44qX8H","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_f2b57774ca7846bd9418f28d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-007 â€” K8s Reconciler æŽ§åˆ¶å™¨\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n\n## Overview\n\nBuild a Kubernetes reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` that manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter workloads using the generated client-go library.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: WorkloadManager Reconciler Structure\n\n**GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentCube CRDs installed  \n**WHEN** the WorkloadManager controller starts  \n**THEN** it initializes with:\n- A typed clientset (`clientset/versioned.Interface`)\n- An informer factory (`informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory`)\n- Listers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1`)\n- Work queue for async reconciliation (`workqueue.RateLimitingInterface`)\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n1. **Controller initialization**\n   - GIVEN a valid `rest.Config`\n   - WHEN `NewWorkloadManager(config)` is called\n   - THEN a `WorkloadManager` instance is returned with initialized clientset, informers, and work queue\n\n2. **Informer registration**\n   - GIVEN a WorkloadManager instance\n   - WHEN informers are started via `Start(stopCh)`\n   - THEN AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers register event handlers (Add/Update/Delete)\n\n3. **Lister wiring**\n   - GIVEN running informers\n   - WHEN a reconciliation cycle begins\n   - THEN listers provide cached read access without API server calls\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: AgentRuntime Reconciliation\n\n**GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR is created/updated/deleted  \n**WHEN** the informer triggers an event  \n**THEN** the reconciler:\n- Enqueues the resource key (`namespace/name`) into the work queue\n- Processes the resource in the worker goroutine\n- Updates `AgentRuntime.status` with current state\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n1. **Create flow**\n   - GIVEN an AgentRuntime CR with `spec.image=volcanoai/agent:latest`\n   - WHEN the CR is created\n   - THEN status.conditions includes `Ready=False` with reason `Pending`\n\n2. **Update flow**\n   - GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime with `spec.replicas=1`\n   - WHEN updated to `spec.replicas=3`\n   - THEN the reconciler scales associated workloads and updates status\n\n3. **Delete flow**\n   - GIVEN an AgentRuntime CR\n   - WHEN the CR is deleted\n   - THEN associated resources are cleaned up and finalizer removed\n\n4. **Status update**\n   - GIVEN successful workload creation\n   - WHEN reconciliation completes\n   - THEN `status.conditions` includes `Ready=True` with `lastTransitionTime`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: CodeInterpreter Reconciliation\n\n**GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter CR lifecycle event  \n**WHEN** the informer notifies the controller  \n**THEN** the reconciler manages the CodeInterpreter lifecycle with status tracking\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n1. **Create flow**\n   - GIVEN a CodeInterpreter CR with `spec.runtimeRef=<agent-runtime-name>`\n   - WHEN the CR is created\n   - THEN the reconciler validates `runtimeRef` exists and sets status\n\n2. **Runtime not found**\n   - GIVEN a CodeInterpreter with `spec.runtimeRef=nonexistent`\n   - WHEN reconciliation runs\n   - THEN status.conditions includes `Ready=False` with reason `RuntimeNotFound`\n\n3. **Successful binding**\n   - GIVEN valid runtimeRef and CodeInterpreter\n   - WHEN reconciliation succeeds\n   - THEN status.phase=`Running` with connection details\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Error Handling & Retry\n\n**GIVEN** a reconciliation failure  \n**WHEN** the worker processes a failing resource  \n**THEN** the item is requeued with exponential backoff\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n1. **Transient error**\n   - GIVEN a temporary API server error\n   - WHEN reconciliation fails\n   - THEN the item is requeued with rate-limited delay\n\n2. **Permanent error**\n   - GIVEN invalid spec (e.g., invalid image format)\n   - WHEN reconciliation fails\n   - THEN status.conditions records the error and item is NOT requeued indefinitely\n\n3. **Retry limit**\n   - GIVEN repeated failures (>maxRetries)\n   - WHEN the worker processes the item\n   - THEN the item is forgotten from the work queue and status marked as `Failed`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Graceful Shutdown\n\n**GIVEN** the controller receives shutdown signal  \n**WHEN** `Shutdown()` is called  \n**THEN** it:\n- Closes the work queue\n- Waits for in-flight reconciliations to complete\n- Shuts down the informer factory\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n1. **Signal handling**\n   - GIVEN a running controller\n   - WHEN SIGTERM is received\n   - THEN `Shutdown()` is invoked within 1 second\n\n2. **Work queue drain**\n   - GIVEN pending items in work queue\n   - WHEN shutdown begins\n   - THEN workers complete current items before exiting (or timeout after 30s)\n\n3. **Informer shutdown**\n   - GIVEN running informers\n   - WHEN `Shutdown()` completes\n   - THEN informer goroutines are terminated and watch connections closed\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Event Recording\n\n**GIVEN** significant reconciliation events  \n**WHEN** status changes occur  \n**THEN** Kubernetes events are emitted via `record.EventRecorder`\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n1. **Normal event**\n   - GIVEN successful AgentRuntime creation\n   - WHEN reconciliation completes\n   - THEN a `Normal` event with reason `AgentRuntimeCreated` is emitted\n\n2. **Warning event**\n   - GIVEN failed reconciliation due to missing runtime\n   - WHEN error is recorded\n   - THEN a `Warning` event with reason `RuntimeNotFound` is emitted\n\n3. **Event aggregation**\n   - GIVEN repeated similar events\n   - WHEN events are emitted\n   - THEN Kubernetes aggregates them (count increments, `lastTimestamp` updates)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Concurrency Control\n\n**GIVEN** multiple resources requiring reconciliation  \n**WHEN** events arrive concurrently  \n**THEN** the controller processes them with controlled parallelism\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n1. **Worker pool**\n   - GIVEN N resources enqueued simultaneously\n   - WHEN workers process them\n   - THEN at most `maxConcurrentReconciles` (default=4) run in parallel\n\n2. **Resource-level locking**\n   - GIVEN the same resource updated twice rapidly\n   - WHEN both events enqueue\n   - THEN duplicate keys are deduplicated in the work queue\n\n3. **No deadlocks**\n   - GIVEN concurrent AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter reconciliations\n   - WHEN they access shared resources\n   - THEN no deadlock or race conditions occur (verified via `go test -race`)\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n| Component | Interface | Usage |\n|-----------|-----------|-------|\n| `clientset.Interface` | `RuntimeV1alpha1()` | Typed CRUD operations |\n| `informers.SharedInformerFactory` | `Runtime().V1alpha1()` | Event streaming + caching |\n| `listers.AgentRuntimeLister` | `Get()/List()` | Read-only cached access |\n| `workqueue.RateLimitingInterface` | `Add()/Get()/Done()` | Async processing with backoff |\n| `record.EventRecorder` | `Event()/Eventf()` | Kubernetes event emission |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `k8s.io/client-go` v0.34.1\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery` v0.34.1\n- `k8s.io/utils` (pointer helpers)\n- Generated client code: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775845418265,"end":1775845418275}}}}
